<subSubSection lastPageId="28" lastPageNumber="52" pageId="27" pageNumber="51" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="27.[837,1468,1728,2016]" pageId="27" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[839,975,1728,1752]" pageId="27" pageNumber="51">Description</emphasis>
(
<specimenCount box="[995,1017,1728,1752]" pageId="27" pageNumber="51" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
, 
<specimenCount box="[1033,1053,1728,1752]" pageId="27" pageNumber="51" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
). Relatively large blackish fly, with sexually dimorphic dark wing markings; agreeing with description of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2015" box="[993,1134,1788,1811]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monstrans">
<emphasis box="[993,1134,1788,1811]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="51">B. monstrans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
except as indicated.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[837,1468,1728,2016]" pageId="27" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis box="[869,994,1816,1840]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="51">Coloration.</emphasis>
Head: antenna tawny-yellow. Thorax black to brown-black. Wing markings of female resembling those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2015" box="[866,1005,1876,1899]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monstrans">
<emphasis box="[866,1005,1876,1899]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="51">B. monstrans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, except that discal crossvein lies completely within transverse brown band (
<figureCitation box="[1168,1248,1904,1928]" captionStart="Figures 48–51" captionStartId="27.[167,239,1461,1483]" captionTargetBox="[167,1465,151,1450]" captionTargetId="figure-230@27.[167,1467,151,1450]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="Figures 48–51. Bama papuanum (Hennig). (48) Right wing of female (holotype of X. papuana). (49) Right wing of male (holotype of X. strigata). (50) Humeral region of right wing of female, showing microtrichia on membrane. (51) Mid coxae of male from right side." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4684918" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4684918/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="51">Fig. 48</figureCitation>
); in male distal dark zone reduced to narrow brown margin on costal section from vein 2 to vein 4 and brown stripe on apical part of vein 4 (
<figureCitation box="[920,999,1992,2016]" captionStart="Figures 48–51" captionStartId="27.[167,239,1461,1483]" captionTargetBox="[167,1465,151,1450]" captionTargetId="figure-230@27.[167,1467,151,1450]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="Figures 48–51. Bama papuanum (Hennig). (48) Right wing of female (holotype of X. papuana). (49) Right wing of male (holotype of X. strigata). (50) Humeral region of right wing of female, showing microtrichia on membrane. (51) Mid coxae of male from right side." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4684918" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4684918/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="51">Fig. 49</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4684920" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4684920" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4684920/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="52" startId="28.[204,275,1222,1244]" targetBox="[206,1338,208,1196]" targetPageId="28">
<paragraph blockId="28.[204,1339,1221,1270]" pageId="28" pageNumber="52">
Figures 52, 53. 
<emphasis box="[345,385,1222,1243]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="52">(52)</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="(Hennig)" authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2001" baseAuthorityName="Hennig" baseAuthorityYear="1940" box="[391,643,1222,1244]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="papuanum">
